aa-11e6-8f41-ea6ed597e4ca"> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-slide wp-volt-gal-photo" data-buy="false" data-caption="Casey Affleck reacts as he accepts the Oscar for best actor for “Manchester by the Sea.”" data-credit="Lucy Nicholson/Reuters" data-image="https://img.washingtonpost.com/rw/2010-2019/WashingtonPost/2017/02/27/Style/Images/2017-02-27T045430Z_1894564130_HP1ED2R0DMT10_RTRMADP_3_AWARDS-OSCARS.jpg?env=A" data-max-width="3307" data-ratio="1.528" data-title=" " data-uuid="1af2c026-fca9-11e6-8f41-ea6ed597e4ca"> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-slide wp-volt-gal-photo" data-buy="false" data-caption="Damien Chazelle accepts the award for best director for “La La Land” from actor Halle Berry." data-credit="Kevin Winter/Getty Images" data-image="https://img.washingtonpost.com/rw/2010-2019/WashingtonPost/2017/02/27/Style/Images/645714854.jpg?env=A" data-max-width="3128" data-ratio="1.281" data-title=" " data-uuid="c818e6d6-fcb3-11e6-8f41-ea6ed597e4ca"> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-slide wp-volt-gal-photo" data-buy="false" data-caption="Amy Adams presents the award for best adapted screenplay." data-credit="Chris Pizzello/Invision via AP" data-image="https://img.washingtonpost.com/rw/2010-2019/WashingtonPost/2017/02/27/Style/Images/89th_Academy_Awards_-_Show_32555-05963.jpg?env=A" data-max-width="2061" data-ratio="0.687" data-title=" " data-uuid="7c6c99a8-fcb3-11e6-8f41-ea6ed597e4ca"> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-slide wp-volt-gal-photo" data-buy="false" data-caption="Tarell Alvin McCraney, right, and Barry Jenkins accept the award for best adapted screenplay for “Moonlight.”" data-credit="Matt Sayles/Invision/AP" data-image="https://img.washingtonpost.com/rw/2010-2019/WashingtonPost/2017/02/27/Style/Images/89th_Academy_Awards_-_Backstage_69992-26c0d.jpg?env=A" data-max-width="3000" data-ratio="1.387" data-title=" " data-uuid="efdd112e-fcae-11e6-8f41-ea6ed597e4ca"> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-slide wp-volt-gal-photo" data-buy="false" data-caption="Kenneth Lonergan accepts the award for best original screenplay for “Manchester by the Sea” from Ben Affleck and Matt Damon. " data-credit="Kevin Winter/Getty Images" data-image="https://img.washingtonpost.com/rw/2010-2019/WashingtonPost/2017/02/27/Style/Images/645710638.jpg?env=A" data-max-width="5196" data-ratio="1.486" data-title=" " data-uuid="8f1e8cc6-fca6-11e6-8f41-ea6ed597e4ca"> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-slide wp-volt-gal-photo" data-buy="false" data-caption="Scarlett Johansson arrives on stage to present the Oscar for best original song." data-credit="Mark Ralston/AFP via Getty Images" data-image="https://img.washingtonpost.com/rw/2010-2019/WashingtonPost/2017/02/27/Style/Images/AFP_M41CR.jpg?env=A" data-max-width="3371" data-ratio="1.5" data-title=" " data-uuid="d65003ba-fca4-11e6-8f41-ea6ed597e4ca"> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-slide wp-volt-gal-photo" data-buy="false" data-caption="Justin Hurwitz, Justin Paul and Benj Pasek win the best original song Oscar for “City of Stars,” featured in “La La Land.” " data-credit="Mark Ralston/AFP/Getty Images" data-image="https://img.washingtonpost.com/rw/2010-2019/WashingtonPost/2017/02/27/Style/Images/AFP_M41KS.jpg?env=A" data-max-width="3816" data-ratio="1.5" data-title=" " data-uuid="ff333e5e-fca5-11e6-8f41-ea6ed597e4ca"> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-slide wp-volt-gal-photo" data-buy="false" data-caption="Samuel L. Jackson presents the Oscar for best original score to Justin Hurwitz for “La La Land.”" data-credit="Lucy Nicholson/Reuters" data-image="https://img.washingtonpost.com/rw/2010-2019/WashingtonPost/2017/02/27/Style/Images/2017-02-27T041824Z_1408564783_HP1ED2R0BYNXY_RTRMADP_3_AWARDS-OSCARS.jpg?env=A" data-max-width="3500" data-ratio="1.37" data-title=" " data-uuid="0ff239f4-fca4-11e6-8f41-ea6ed597e4ca"> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-slide wp-volt-gal-photo" data-buy="false" data-caption="Lin-Manuel Miranda appears on screen as he reads tweets." data-credit="Chris Pizzello/Invision via AP" data-image="https://i